## Testing Checklist

Before completing testing work:

- [ ] Tested all core functionality
- [ ] Tested all user/actor types (see project context)
- [ ] Tested error scenarios
- [ ] Tested edge cases
- [ ] Verified UI responsiveness (desktop and mobile)
- [ ] Tested API endpoints (gRPC and REST)
- [ ] Created bug reports for all non-critical issues found
- [ ] Documented critical bugs that were fixed
- [ ] Updated backlog README with new bug entries

## Testing Workflow

1. **Start Application**
   - See project context for run commands and ports (backend, gateway, frontend)

2. **Execute Test Plan**
   - Follow systematic testing approach
   - Document findings as you go
   - Take screenshots/logs for bug reports

3. **Create Bug Reports**
   - Use the bug report template
   - Follow naming convention
   - Update backlog README

4. **Verify Critical Fixes**
   - If fixing critical bugs, verify the fix works
   - Run integration tests
   - Test the specific scenario that was broken

